          <h2 class="games-column-header">Investopedia Simulator</h2>
          <div class="text-container">
            <p class="games-column-text">Test your trading skills without risking a dime. The Investopedia Stock Market Simulator gives you a virtual portfolio to buy and sell stocks, ETFs, and options in real-time market conditions. With built-in tools and financial news, it’s a great way to practice investment strategies, understand market behavior, and get comfortable with the mechanics of trading.</p>
            <p class="games-column-text">For STEM students exploring financial literacy, this simulator offers a risk-free environment to build confidence in investing. Whether you’re experimenting with technical analysis or just learning what a ticker symbol is, this tool makes abstract financial concepts tangible.</p>
          </div>
          {{> components/buttons/mark-done-button taskID="2" taskType="game" link="https://www.investopedia.com/simulator/portfolio" button-text="Play Now"}}
